       Check the loan agreement below:<br/>
       <b>Notice</b><br/>

The loan process will take approximately six months. Loan requests should be sent to the house six months before the date when you wish to receive the loan. Only in exceptional circumstances will a request be considered in a shorter period.

<br/><b>Length of loan</b><br/>

Long-term loans are for 3-5 years (to be agreed) and can be extended at the end of the loan period if both parties agree.

<br/><b>Costs</b><br/>

The borrower is responsible for covering all costs of the loan, including, but not restricted to the following: cleaning, conservation, preparation, mounting, framing, packing, transport, courier, insurance, installation, security.

<br/><b>Insurance</b><br/>

A recent and realistic value for the object will be provided by the lender. The borrower is responsible for insuring the object nail-to-nail and shelf-to-shelf under a fully-comprehensive fine arts or museum policy which is agreed by the lender. State Indemnity will be accepted as an alternative to commercial insurance. A copy of the insurance or indemnity certificate, naming the lending institution as “additional insured” will be sent to the lender before the loan begins.
 <b>If the borrower fails to provide the loan, the lender can confiscate the object (House in this case), after a period of 3 months. </b>             
